cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.AI, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with an evolutionary algorithm and its performance analysis. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper provides bounds on the expected proportion of fit individuals in the population. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper discusses the performance of EAs on 2-SAT and Set Cover problems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper deals with an optimization algorithm commonly used in AI. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper provides upper bounds on the runtime of EAs on certain problems.
